div.div:
Before continuing it makes sure that:
filter_is_initialized
measurement doesn't come from the past(otherwise ignore)
If time_triggered:
adds measurement to measurement_buffer
If data_triggered:
calls predict step from FilterT
calls update step from FilterT
updates the time_keeper
We could call both temporial- and observatgion_update of FilterBase from process_measurement, but for the time_triggered case we wouldn't be able to do only a temporial_update if it happens that we are not receiving any measurement and need to do only temporial_update.
